00:03:13.000 --> 00:04:33.000
<h1>Some figures [WHO]</h1>
<h2>In the world</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1 billion people (15% of the world's population)</li>
  <li>Probably underestimated</li>
  <li>On the rise (progress of medicine, demographic aging)</li>
</ul>
<h2>In developing countries</h2>
<ul>
  <li>80% of PWD</li>
</ul>
<h2>In countries with life expectancy greater than 70 years</h2>
<ul>
  <li>People live on average 8 years with disabilities (11.5% lifespan)</li>
</ul>

7
00:04:33.000 --> 00:06:20.000
<h1>Disability figures</h1>
<h2>Note</h2>
<ul>
  <li>It's easy to find numbers but hard to make them consistent</li>
  <li>Why?
    <ul>
      <li>At the global level, the quality of censuses is variable</li>
      <li>Studies often fragmented (only one type of handicap)</li>
      <li>Recensement vs declaration</li>
      <li>Functional aspects and activity limitations but also subjective perceptions</li>
      <li>The word "disability" covers very different realities</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Need to define terms and what they cover</li>
</ul>

